column5: Has anyone gotten back reently from Minaki? I read the other post just curious if there is any even more recnt information on Minaki. Leaving Saturday...any certain spots, depths, or presentations working well? Thanks for the infor and Rob if you read this I will stop and introduce myself on Saturday. Thanks, Slim

I am going to be leaving for Minaki on Saturday as well. It will be my first time there. Where are you staying? I think I am staying at a place called Rich's or Richard's. I guess it is not really a resort but just a guy who rents out a few cabins. I too would be interested in a more recent fishing report. Also, does anybody now where you can look at some maps of the Minaki area on the internet? I haven't found much as of yet.

We just got back Sunday nite from Minaki, we stayed at Paradise Cove 1, we were camping. The Walleyes are stacked up on Claybanks, there were 4 guys nexted to us got their limits in 2 1/2 hours, we had motor trouble so we came home, but everyone ya talk to are limiting out with nice Walleyes and the big Northerns are hitting and even a few Muskies. We are going back, so let us know how you do.[email protected]
P>S Mille Lacs Guy There are maps of the lakes at most of the resorts up there. Good Luck pikelady
